# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  offhook-agent keys.  Copy this file to `.env` and fill in only what you need:
#      cp .env.example .env
#  offhook-agent auto-loads `.env` from the working directory. `.env` is gitignored —
#  your keys never leave your machine, and offhook-agent never stores them anywhere.
#  Run `offhook-agent doctor` any time to see exactly what's SET vs MISSING.
#
#  You do NOT need all of these. The tiers below build up:
#      Tier 1 (one key)  → talk to your agent in the terminal      (offhook-agent chat)
#      Tier 2 (+ LiveKit)→ talk to it in your browser              (offhook-agent dev)
#      Tier 3 (+ carrier)→ answer a real phone number              (offhook-agent phone)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Tier 1 · THE BRAIN — pick ONE LLM provider (required for anything) ────────
# OpenAI — in the single-key default this ALSO powers STT + TTS, so one key is
# enough for the whole voice pipeline.   https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# …or OpenRouter (one key, every hosted model: GPT, Qwen, DeepSeek, Llama…).
# Set models.llm.provider: openrouter in agent.yaml.   https://openrouter.ai/keys
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# …or run a model locally with Ollama — NO key needed. Set models.llm.provider:
# ollama in agent.yaml, and `ollama serve`.            https://ollama.com


# ── Tier 2 · LIVE VOICE — required to talk in the browser or on the phone ─────
# LiveKit Cloud is free and has SIP built in.  Create a project, then copy these
# from Settings → Keys.                                https://cloud.livekit.io
# LIVEKIT_URL=wss://your-project.livekit.cloud
# LIVEKIT_API_KEY=
# LIVEKIT_API_SECRET=

# Optional production-quality speech (the single OpenAI key above already works):
# Deepgram STT (nova-3)                                https://console.deepgram.com
# DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=
# Cartesia TTS (sonic-3)                               https://play.cartesia.ai/keys
# CARTESIA_API_KEY=
# ElevenLabs TTS                          https://elevenlabs.io/app/settings/api-keys
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=


# ── Tier 3 · PHONE — only to answer a real number (offhook-agent phone) ─────────────
# Your LiveKit SIP endpoint (LiveKit Cloud shows it in the project's SIP page).
# LIVEKIT_SIP_URI=sip:your-project.sip.livekit.cloud

# Pick ONE carrier:
# Twilio — Account SID + Auth Token are on the console home page.
#                                                      https://console.twilio.com
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=

# …or Telnyx — create a v2 API key.       https://portal.telnyx.com  (API Keys)
# TELNYX_API_KEY=


# ── Optional · MESSAGE DELIVERY — so "take a message" actually lands ──────────
# Twilio SMS reuses TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID + TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN above (set tools.delivery: sms).
# Resend (email)                                       https://resend.com/api-keys
# RESEND_API_KEY=
